cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.NE 

The paper deals with content-based image retrieval (CBIR) using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and Radon transform. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves feature extraction and classification, which are common topics in information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM). The use of neural networks suggests a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
